A former senator, Shehu Sani, is back on the social media after a month away in the detention center of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission. Sani also thanked Nigerians for supporting him during his detention and trial. The former lawmaker representing Kaduna Central Senatorial district at the National Assembly was arrested by the anti-graft agency for allegedly collecting $24,000 from the Chairman of ASD Motors, Alhaji Sani Dauda to bribe Acting Chairman of EFCC, Ibrahim Magu.



